cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CY 

This paper discusses probabilistic reasoning and its explanation, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study also involves human reasoning under uncertainty, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the presentation of explanations to users, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) as users need to be able to control the style and completeness of explanations to ensure privacy and security.
